messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path:
- /cms/admin/group/{gid}

All methods acceptable:
- False

Per-method acceptability (based on the code only):
- HEAD: False
- POST: False
- OPTIONS: False
- TRACE: False
- GET: True
- PUT: False
- DELETE: False
- PATCH: False

Explanation (concise):
- Path composition: create_cms() is registered with url_prefix "/cms" in app.register_blueprints (app/__init__.py). create_cms() registers admin_api with url_prefix "/admin" (app/api/cms/__init__.py). The get_group view in app/api/cms/admin.py is decorated with @admin_api.route("/group/<int:gid>"), so the full route is /cms + /admin + /group/<int:gid> â†’ /cms/admin/group/{gid} (path parameter shown as {gid}).
- Methods: The get_group route decorator does not include a methods argument, so only the GET-handling view is defined in code for this function. Therefore GET is acceptable. Although the same path has other view functions later in the file that explicitly handle PUT and DELETE, those are separate endpoints (different view functions) and do not make PUT/DELETE acceptable for the get_group function. Per the instruction to base decisions strictly on the code (not on framework runtime behavior), HEAD and OPTIONS are not marked acceptable because they are not explicitly declared in the source for this view.
